name: Men Tinggen Nasi Bali
address: 8782+656, Jl. Pajang Sari, Sanur Kauh, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80227, Indonesia
review 1: Really good! They have a chicken rice set and pork rice set. Both were good and really affordable. It costs you only 20k each. The meat they provided, the floss, and lawar was excellent. Their sambal is also spicy and nice. Overall, will come to this place again for my next trip.
review 2:
One of the legendary balinese warung that can be found in Sanur. It is open until late night and they have several menus like nasi campur ayam, nasi campur babi, or even nasi campur ayam dan babi. The place for the food is seperate so if you dont eat babi / pork, it is still fine since they keep seperate between pork and chicken. The parking space also big and you have to pay for the parking fee. The staff is very hospitable and ready to serve you

My personal observation based on scale 1 to 5, from very bad, bad, okay, good, very good.

Taste: 4/5
Price: 4/5
Parking area: 5/5
Staff: 5/5
Location: 5/5
Recommended: yes if you are wondering to have some late dinner, this one i recommend to you
review 3:
Taste is likely balinesse meals with strong spices and many herbs. Good food for pleasure balinesse tounge especially for lawar and pork meat.
Spacious parking area are available, they open until after midnight good choice for supper portion.
review 4: This place is famos for their Nasi Lawar, one of Bali‚Äôs traditional food. They have chicken and pork for the options. The place is quite far away and the place is like outdoor food stall. The place was visited mostly by locals, it‚Äôs my second time here and I‚Äôve seen no tourist. The taste of the food was very good. If you want to try something new, come here and tru their Nasi Lawar.
review 5: Very best for Nasi Campur in here!!! The taste it's not heavy but lite and delicious even small restaurant inside the public market look clean and comfortable. Btw they have picture with artists and my lovely President also.

name: Goddes Bakery
address: Jl. Danau Buyan No.5b, Sanur, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80227, Indonesia
review 1:
Looking for a good breakfast, lunch, and dinner in Sanur area? I highly recomended this place.

Good food, good price, good vibes, and the food was awesome, i try the pork ribs myself, it was tender and juicy, also their dessert is amazing.

You should try this if you in sanur area.
review 2:
I ordered Braised Oxtail and Chicken Cashew.
As I am not a big fan of rice I changed the Chicken Cashew side to Fries.
The oxtail was piping hot, well cooked and very tasty. The Chicken Cashew was served piping hot and well cooked.  The side of fries were the best fries I have eaten in Bali.(8 years) Hot, crispy and plentyful.
review 3: I can recommend this Cafe, the food quality is consistently good. The ambience is more practical than cosy or stylish. But better like this than the other way around. You can see and taste that the owner is the chef. Prices are reasonable and the location is still in reach of the main tourist area.
review 4:
Incredibly delicious cakes for cheap money.

The place appears clean and calm.

Friendly staff. tasty and cheap for high quality

I can really recommend Goddes Bakery in Sanur
review 5:
Lovely place.
Helpful and friendly attentive staff.
Great quality pastry in the danish. Really top drawer stuff.
Good coffee.
Excellent french fries with the tasty sandwich.
Salad dressing was a revalation!! Possibly roasted garlic vinaigrette. A little touch of vanilla this stuff would be 100%
Must give it a try! They gojek and do take away too. Lovely secluded garden to sip and sit outside.

address: Jl. Penyaringan No.99 KM, Sanur Kauh, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80227, Indonesia
review 1:
We got this villa via TikTok. The staff are nice
but the room needs refurbishing badly. The bed creaks so bad as if it will break any time. Sliding door is stuck all the time. Open air shower leaks. Other than that it‚Äôs a quiet place. Good for doing work. WiFi reception is good. Pool is 5 feet deep.
review 2: Quiet place, good quality bed, clean & proper room, not far from Denpasar
review 3: Beautiful 2 bedroom  bungalow with private courtyard and pool . No cooking facilities in this bungalow however does have a fridge. Very clean, well kept gardens and surrounds. Breakfast included which is eggs, toast, juice ,fruit and tea / coffee. Staff are lovely and helpful.  It isn't close to town or beaches. However it is a cheap taxi ride of AU around $2.50 - $3.50. Beware of what taxi service you get as price can vary . Cabs with meters are recommended and make sure they turn it on .Quiet location amongst quality homes.
review 4:
Pros: Good villa. The room is very clean. The staff is friendly. Great view.
Cons: the shower is leaking when I turn it on. I can't make a difference between a shampoo bottle and a soap bcs there's no name in it. And sometimes the water heater is not working.
review 5: Worst experience. Bedding is no.1 aspect for me to decide where to stay. This place is by far the worst. Bedding is basically a waterproof plastic and pillows stinks. Hair everywhere which are NOT mine. Had to dust off millions of bugs and its parts from bedding for a while before use it. Dirty room, dust and hair at every corner. Shower sucks as well. Hot water for 2 mins then gets cold. Mine does not even has mirror nor tooth brush etc kind of bath kit. Naturally no hair dryer. Breakfast is even more ridiculous. No need to explain the menu, it does not have coffee. For drinks, you have only one option, orange juice. Seriously?? The pool was too dark after sunset to get in. The staff seems totally and totally untrained. I would ever recommand this place. I was way too naive to believe those nice reviews. BTW, I was staying in 2br villa. Oh and no kitchen...sort of things except a fridge.

name: Oxy House Bali
address: Jl. Danau Tondano IV No.7, Sanur, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80228, Indonesia
review 1: Lived in the year 2023, around 3 weeks, the hotel is situated in a relatively quiet and peaceful location, the staff is kind and responsive, and the added benefit was a mini-kitchen. The rooms are clean and spacious, and the air conditioner works well. As a drawback, I would note the replacement of bed linen every 10 days. But overall, we are very satisfied.
review 2:
My parents stayed in Oxy House for 2 month in June und July 2023. I live nearby so it was a perfect location for them to stay during their visit.

My parents are elderly people and they need some assistance. Lina and her mother were always super helpful with everything. I had a good feeling to book an apartment for my parents there because there is always a staff member present and Lina is always available on WhatsApp.

Oxy House is a cozy place with a family atmosphere, a pool and apartments with an own kitchen. Lina and her mum take care about everything, Maxi and Komang are cleaning and maintain the place. All are very welcoming and caring. My parents even got sometimes food from Lina and a cake for my dad's birthday. If there was a problem they responded fast and fixed it.

Oxy House is located in Sanur Kauh which is a less touristic area. If you stay there you can experience local balinese live combined with western standard living. The beach is around 5 minutes by scooter, supermarkets, laundry and some small restaurants are in walking distance.

Thank you Lina & Team for everything!
review 3: a great place to stay with children - a separate kitchen, two bedrooms, a clean pool. we lived here for three months (November 2022-January 2023). a big plus of this house in its owners - beautiful women with kindness and understanding treated not only our desires, but also the antics of our children. thanks to them for that! If we are in Bali again, we will definitely stay in this house! Lina, thank you so much!!!
review 4: It was quiet alright, room is big with hot water, kitchen. Swimming Pool and they do not provided breakfast the owner will help you for order online food near by the hotel. I Stayed at room number 4, the AC was not cool need clean up. At bath room any hole of ants under of wash basin, not bad but need more attention. so far I will back again staying at another room.
review 5: We had a lovely stay here. We are a family of four, they made sure we had a cot and the rooms were always cleaned, the staff we always friendly and helpful and the price was excellent. It‚Äôs very basic but we had a nice stay for two weeks.

name: Casa Yasa Sanur
address: Gg. III No.4, Sanur Kauh, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80227, Indonesia
review 1: Casa Yasa is THE perfect home away from home for travellers. A very modern building with excellent WiFi, air-con, en-suite bathrooms, fridges, free water, a good shared outdoor kitchen and very new smart TVs that actually work. It's also very secure. It's run by a clued-up sister and brother and their family live in a traditional Balinese home just next door. If you ask them where is a surf club, restaurant, doctor, dentist, print shop or anything they'll give you the proper answer of a local who knows how to navigate real life in Denpasar. There's a massive fresh food market around the corner every morning (a few places stay open until later) and a western food supermarket nearby too (you gotta pay for that cheese and butter!). It's a shortish walk away from the noise of touristy Sanur beaches and there aren't many tourist bars, restaurants or spas on your doorstep but you can just walk there in 15 mins when you want it like that. There's loads of very late opening cash-only stores nearby and a bigger late-night 7-11 style store nearby. Lots of semi-permanent residents stay here and they're very welcoming to people no matter what lifestyle you have. If you want to mingle, you can mingle. If you don't then no problem. It's a modern wing of a traditional Balinese way of life. If you want cocktail stick umbrellas it's not for you and the only petals-in-the-hair action is when grandma blesses the place for morning and evening puja. If you can get a room here go for it.
review 2: Lovely place to stay in a really convenient location for getting around in Sanur. Close to the beach, morning/night markets, shopping, supermarkets and there are so many great food options near by. The building is new, super clean & very well maintained. The owners are lovely people and they take such great care of the rooms & the beautiful garden. You really notice the thoroughness of the regular cleaning. Fully equipped gorgeous new share kitchen. Icy cold air con in the rooms. Really comfortable beds in the rooms and the upstairs rooms especially get a beautiful sea breeze, and stunning sunset views of Mt Batur & sunrise views of Mt Agung. Highly recommend üòä
review 3: Loved the peaceful ambience .A homely , comfortable, neat and affordable property . Would not be wrong to call it ‚Äòa home away from home‚Äô. Easy access to nearby markets and beaches too. And great service to top it all. Definitely booking it again!! üëç
review 4: Comfortable room with clean bath facilities. Local family owned with strong staff support. Convenient location to shopping, markets, and beaches. I hope to visit again soon.
review 5: What a great place and location!!  Beautiful in every way‚Ä¶.We had the time of our life! Hope to be back sooner than later!

address: Jl. Gn. Sari Gg. VIII No.1j, Sanur Kauh, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80227, Indonesia
review 1: We live here more then one year, really nice kost have kitchen and clean bathroom, the area quite just next to rice fields you can walk to the traditional market intaran about 3 minutes many delicious local food or western food around kost kubu d‚Äôcarik . The landlord also really nice and neighbors too üòä
review 2: Me and my wife spend two months here and we love every minute of it. in terms of location, this place is located in a strategic place. close to literally everything. Sanur beach, Renon, Bali Mandara Hospital, Traditional Markets, and is surrounded by so many good food merchants. The place itself is clean, very quiet, and super comfortable. We would love to stay longer here but unfortunately, we have to go back to our hometown due to work commitments. We'll be back here if we come back to Bali. Suksma Pak Agung!
review 3:
i stayed here for few months.
PERFECT place to stay, cozy, comfortable and quiet place to have some rest after work or exhausting duty or holiday.
price is reasonable
they have parking area
friendly owner
unfortunately i need to move because of my job.
but if company send me to duty again in Bali Absolutely i will booked this room for my stay.
RECOMENDED 100%
review 4: Cannot fault this accomodation. Room is lovely. Kitchen is a adequate. Bathroom is great with hot water. Lovely quiet location and Landlord is great. Would recommend this to anyone looking for a kost. You would struggle to find anywhere better for the money.
review 5:
I stayed at Kost Kubu di Carik for many months. I lived in Bali for long time and I changed kost many times until I found this one, which for me is the BEST place I have ever lived in.
The quality/price ratio is absolutely excellent: the kost features new furniture, tiles and finishings, it is fully equipped with AC, hot water, TV, wifi and it also has small kitchen area, wardrobe and a super comfortable bed including very fine quality bedsheets.
The inside of the rooms is very well designed, it is luminous and super clean.
Anyway, I think the best part of this place is the garden and the quiet surrounding: the kost is located at the very end of a super quiet gang and it is facing ricefields.
I will always remember the amazing stunning sunset views as I came back home from a long day of work and the incredible good sleep at night when the only sound is the chant of the crickets :)
Also, the place has only 5 rooms so even when full occupancy it is very very quiet.
Location is north Sanur, only 5 min ride with  bike to the closest beach - Pantai Segara.
Nonetheless, Pak Arya - the owner - is a superb helpful nice man that takes care of the place with dedication and will be there for you when you need help.
I recommend Kost Kubu di Carik with all my heart and I will always remember this place.
If I hadn't decided to go back home, I would definately stay here forever!
Thank you pak Arya for your help and kindness!
